  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1"/>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date when="1873-07-12">July 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#wileyeda">Edward</persName>:</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          Your letter arrived yesterday<lb/> and as your time is growing so short<lb/> in Pittsburg, it seems important that my<lb/> answer should not be delayed.
        </p>
        <p>
          I think <persName ref="#stillcavm">Carrie</persName> has carried your<lb/> letter off as I do not find it on my desk<lb/> and she has not come down to breakfast<lb/> yet. However I will go on answering<lb/> from memory.
        </p>
        <p>
	      A.G. Carroll, No 52 St. Mary St.<lb/> Baltimore is the name of the gentleman<lb/> who wrote me the 3rd of April for a copy<lb/> of the Turkey Morocco U.G.R.R.<lb/> I hope you will have the good luck<lb/> to get off all your books in <placeName><choice><sic>Pittsburg</sic><corr>Pittsburgh</corr></choice></placeName>.<lb/>
	      I have not yet received Caugillâ€™s letter<lb/> but am on the lookout for it. I would<lb/> be pleased to have him take an agency.<lb/> Does he mean to apply for a general agency<lb/>? When he writes I shall be ready for<lb/> him.
        </p>
        <p>
	      I think very well of your intention<lb/> of coming home through Baltimore.<lb/> I had an order for Baltimore this<lb/> week but would not fill it. It came
          <add place="top-left" rend="vertical">to me from the<lb/> friends <unclear resp="#jd">Intelligencer's</unclear><lb/> <unclear resp="#jd"/> office</add><!-- text written vertically on the top of the page -->
        </p>
        <closer rend="top-left, vertical">
          <salute>Yours affec.</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W.S.</abbr><expan>William Still</expan></choice> </persName></signed>
        </closer>
    </body>
